\textbf{Independent Events}

If the probability of $A$ happening \underline\text{does not}
change even when $B$ happens \underline\text{and} if the
probability of $B$ happening does not change 
after $A$ occurs, then the two events $A$ and $B$
are said to be \underline\text{independent events}

%
\text{Independence} \implies \[ \begin{cases}
P\left( A\,\vert\, B\right) = P(A) \\ 
P\left( B\,\vert\, A\right) = P(B) 
\end{cases} \]
